Troubleshooting Tips
OSQuery service fails to start:

Check configuration syntax: sudo osqueryd --config_check
Verify permissions on log/database directories
Review logs: sudo journalctl -u osqueryd -n 50
Python scripts return empty results:

Ensure OSQuery is running: sudo systemctl status osqueryd
Verify query syntax in interactive mode: sudo osqueryi
Check file permissions for reading logs
Validate JSON parsing with sample data
No threats detected during testing:

Verify test processes are actually running: ps aux | grep nc
Check threat pattern regex syntax
Ensure sufficient time for OSQuery to log events
Review detection logic and thresholds
